  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6819.8 sitting above the 6797 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are long gamma and will mechanically sell this rally into the massive 6825 (+5.06B) and 6830 (+3.86B) gamma walls, creating natural resistance. The regime flip and 240% GEX surge indicates fresh option positioning has dramatically altered dealer flow dynamics, with the 6700 negative gamma strike now acting as a magnet if we break the flip level. Key levels: defend 6797 flip for continued upside, but expect heavy selling pressure into 6825-6830, with 6900 (+5.17B) representing the ultimate gamma wall where dealer selling intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to get capped around 6825-6830 with dealers selling rallies.",
